# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════
#  Civil Engineering Suite — .gitignore
#  IMPORTANT: The raw HTML files must NEVER be
#  committed to GitHub. Only the .enc files go up.
#
#  FIX (2026-05-29):
#  [F1] Changed bare 'index.html' → '/index.html'
#       Changed bare 'footing-pro/index.html' → '/footing-pro/index.html'
#       Without a leading slash, git matches index.html in EVERY
#       subdirectory — which was silently blocking:
#         footing-pro/engineers/index.html
#         footing-pro/offices/index.html
#         footing-pro/students/index.html
#         beam-pro/index.html (and all other app pages)
#       Leading slash anchors the pattern to the repo root only.
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════

# Raw HTML source — NEVER commit these (anchored to repo root)
/index.html
/footing-pro/index.html

# Encryption key file — NEVER commit this
ENCRYPTION_KEY.txt
*.key
.env
.env.local
.env.production

# Encrypted files DO get committed (they are useless without the key)
# !public/pc_suite.enc
# !public/footing_pro.enc

# OS files
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini

# Editor files
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo

# Node (if you ever add build tools)
node_modules/
.vercel/
PAYMENT_SETUP_GUIDE.md
